HEADWORD: Karaite
<hw>Ka"ra*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Heb.
<ets>q⟦amac⟧r⟦amac⟧</ets> to read.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld>
<def>A sect of Jews who adhere closely to the letter of the Scriptures,
rejecting the oral law, and allowing the Talmud no binding authority; --
opposed to the <contr>Rabbinists</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

